text:
Emergency medical technicians
"-What happened?-I don’t know. Sheriff Truman just brought her in from Glastonbury Grove."
 ― B. Roundtree and First emergency medical technician
In late March 1989, after Annie Blackburn was found bloodied at Glastonbury Grove, two unidentified medical technicians admitted her to Calhoun Memorial Hospital.
